id: hac-wwsi
title: Automate conditional daily releases with lossless pm changelog generation
description: "Adopt pm-cli's daily conditional release model: skip when no publishable changes exist after the latest tag, generate the full changelog from repo-local pm data, prepare a calendar version, verify, push a release commit and tag, publish once to npm with provenance, and prove both npx and bunx consumption."
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 0
tags[6]: automation,bun,github-actions,npm,pm-changelog,release
created_at: "2026-07-21T17:20:42.790Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-21T17:51:50.711Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-21T17:38:23.446Z"
author: codex-root
estimated_minutes: 480
acceptance_criteria: Every pre-existing CHANGELOG.md statement is represented by closed pm lineage and remains visible after full-history generation; Scheduled and manual auto-release skips cleanly when no publishable changes exist since the latest tag; A new tag drives one provenance-backed npm publication and verifies both npx and bunx launch paths
goal: lossless-automatic-releases
objective: conditional-daily-release-parity-with-pm-cli
value: Remove manual release drift without losing historical release knowledge.
impact: "Makes releases repeatable, auditable, and consumable by both Node and Bun users."
outcome: "A documented, tested conditional release pipeline backed by pm-changelog."
why_now: The repository has unreleased changes and only a manual publish workflow; its March history predates repo-local pm tracking.
parent: hac-4s9j
reviewer: unbraind
risk: high
confidence: 95
sprint: release-automation
release: 2026.7.21
resolution: "Delivered the pm-cli-style split auto-release/tag-publish model, lossless pm-changelog migration, npm provenance, Bun consumer verification, CI drift gate, detailed pm evidence, and clean end-to-end dry-run proof."
expected_result: "Changes after the latest release produce at most one checked daily release by default without losing changelog history, and the artifact works through npm and Bun."
actual_result: All child work is closed with evidence; 16/16 legacy statements are preserved; 988 tests and 95.55% statement coverage pass; packed npx/bunx smoke and conditional dry-run pass.
comments[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T17:20:42.790Z",codex-root,The legacy changelog is a migration source of truth and must not be overwritten until every statement has tracker-backed coverage.
  "2026-07-21T17:51:50.692Z",codex-root,"PR review hardening: Commander version discovery and replacement now accept single or double quotes and optional whitespace."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T17:20:42.790Z",codex-root,"Bun consumes packages from the npm registry; publish exactly once to npm, then verify Bun installation and bunx execution instead of attempting a duplicate registry publish."
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T17:20:42.790Z",codex-root,pm-changelog full-history mode assigns explicitly released historical items to their release windows even when those items are backfilled later.
close_reason: "Conditional daily release automation is implemented, documented, tracker-backed, and fully verified"
